  "title": "LORRY DRIVER",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li><strong>Vehicle Operation &amp; Maintenance</strong>:Driving commercial vehicles over varying distances, conducting pre-trip and routine safety checks (e.g., tires, brakes, oil), and reporting any mechanical issues.</li>\n  <li><strong>Loading &amp; Unloading</strong>:Safely loading, securing, and unloading goods or materials, ensuring they are properly stowed and protected during transit.</li>\n  <li><strong>Route &amp; Schedule Management</strong>:Planning efficient routes and delivery schedules, often in coordination with a transport manager, and adapting to traffic reports or diversions.</li>\n  <li><strong>Documentation &amp; Compliance</strong>:Completing and updating delivery logs, trip reports, and other required paperwork, and strictly adhering to traffic, road, and company regulations.</li>\n  <li><strong>Communication</strong>:Liaising with dispatchers or transport managers to report delays, discuss issues, or receive updates on routes and schedules.</li>\n</ul>",
